Since one of the main objectives of this study is to determine optimal DH and PH to maximize GY, correlations between these two traits were calculated per trial (
 Table 
  1
 ). Significant negative correlations between DH and GY were reported in Diyarbakir 2013, Konya 2013, Maragheh 2014, Diyarbakir 2015, and Maragheh 2016 (
 Table 
  1
 ). Correlations (linear associations) between GY and DH in other trials were not significant (
 Table 
  1
 ). PH correlated positively with GY (and statistically significant) in Konya 2013, Maragheh 2013, Konya 2014, Maragheh 2014, and Konya 2015, being those also the environments with lower rainfall (
 Table 
  1
 ). Correlations between GY and PH in other trials were not significant (
 Table 
  1
 ). Using the means of each genotype across locations and years, DH and PH correlated negatively with GY (
 r = -0.40 and 
 r = -0.15; 
 Table 
  3
 ).
